        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued June 15 at 3:27PM EDT by NWS Peachtree City GA</headline>
        <description>At 327 PM EDT, a line of strong thunderstorms was along a line
extending from Higgston to near Workmore, and moving east at 5 mph.

HAZARD...Up to 40 mph wind, frequent cloud to ground lightning and
heavy rain.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Expect minor damage to tree limbs and blowing around of
light, unsecured objects. Heavy rain may cause temporary
street flooding especially in poor drainage areas.

Locations impacted include...
McRae, Lyons, Alamo, Mount Vernon, Vidalia, Helena, Lumber City,
Glenwood, Milan, Uvalda, Stillmore, Oak Park, Ailey, Scotland,
Higgston, Santa Claus, Alston, Towns, Spring Hill, and South
Thompson.
</description>
        <instruction>People outdoors should seek shelter immediately. If you can hear
thunder, you are close enough to be struck by lightning. Motorists
should slow down and be prepared for possible loss of control due to
hydroplaning.</instruction>
